Name: Ascent
checklistText:
<size=22>ASCENT CHECKLIST</size>

Verify platform alignment: FDAI should indicate roll offset for trajectory azimuth

<size=20>T -10 seconds:</size> 
	Computer Mode					- ASC and not running

<size=20>Ignition:</size>
Monitor ENGINE I (2) lt: 
	RED on pressure buildup
	OFF on nominal thrust
Monitor ENGINE II lt:
	AMBER: ready

<size=20>Liftoff:</size>
Monitor computer start & clocks are running
Monitor FUEL 1 OXID
Monitor ALTITIDE
	Abort Mode I: < 15,000 FEET
	Abort Mode I-II: 15,000 TO 75,000 FEET
	Abort Mode II: 75,000 TO 522,000 FEET
	Abort Mode III: ABOVE 522,000 FEET
At 75,000 FEET:	
	D-Ring						- STOW (Use C)

<size=20>When FUEL 1 OXID depleted, staging.:</size>
Monitor ENGINE II lt:
	RED on pressure buildup
	OFF on nominal thrust
Monitor FUEL 2 OXID

<size=20>SSECO and Insertion:</size>
	SPCT SEP Lt					- LUMINATED
	SPCT SEP 					- PUSH
	JETT FAIRING 				- PUSH
	OAMS						- ENABLE 
	IVIs							- "Zero" 
		May need to Zero IVI at Pe.

Note: It might not be possible to fully zero the IVIs. Do as best as you can, but don't force it.

Steps.Text: At T-10: Computer Mode - ASC and not running
Monitor computer start & clocks are running
Monitor ENGINE II lt & FUEL 2 OXID
